main event: A sighting of a possible satellite was reported on May 3, 1964, with a brightness comparable to a first magnitude star, traveling east at a speed of 10 degrees per second.
interesting points: The sighting occurred at coordinates 35.10N 174.40W in the Pacific Ocean., The observation was classified as Air-Visual., The report includes various military organizations and codes related to the sighting., There are multiple conclusions drawn about the object, including it possibly being a balloon, aircraft, or an astronomical object., Communication about the sighting was circulated among various military branches and personnel.
